# Central Tour Monorepo Rules (ENFORCED)

These rules apply **equally and identically** to every app under `apps/*` (today: `apps/b2c`, `apps/b2b`; tomorrow: any new `apps/<name>`). If a rule names a path with `apps/*/...`, read it as "this rule is the same in every app."

The two apps share a product model. Differences are **scale and content**, not architecture:

- b2c and b2b share the **same folder shape**, **same module contract**, and **same boundaries**.
- An app may have **fewer or more pages** in a given module (e.g. `profile` with 2–3 pages in b2c vs 10+ pages in b2b) — that is expected and fine.
- A module may exist in one app and not the other — still fine.
- **What must stay the same:** where code lives, how modules are shaped, how API/state/routing is organized, how shared UI is consumed.

## Core architecture (every app)

- `apps/*/src/app/` = routing ONLY
- DO NOT place UI, hooks, or business logic inside `apps/*/src/app/`
- Pages MUST only compose modules

- ALL features MUST live in `apps/*/src/modules/*`
- Each product domain (flights, hotels, transfers, auth, home, profile, …) is an independent module

- `apps/*/src/shared/` = generic ONLY (app-local utilities, base API client, i18n, app-wide constants)
- `packages/*` = generic ONLY (monorepo-wide: shared UI, shared configs)
- DO NOT put product-specific logic in `shared/` or `packages/`

## Forbidden (never do this, in any app)

- UI inside `apps/*/src/app/`
- Business logic inside `apps/*/src/app/`
- API calls inside React components
- Feature logic inside `apps/*/src/shared/` or `packages/*`
- Cross-module leakage without clear structure
- Forking a UI component per app (override via CSS variables in `apps/*/src/app/globals.css` instead)

## Required patterns (every app)

- Use `apps/*/src/modules/<product>/` for UI, logic, services, types, hooks, pages
- Use `apps/*/src/shared/api` for the base API client
- Use `apps/*/src/modules/*/services` for feature-level API logic
- Prefer server components; use client components ONLY when necessary
- Keep `packages/ui/src/components/ui/*` (shadcn base) as stable primitives
- Build feature variants by composing primitives in `apps/*/src/modules/*`, `apps/*/src/shared/components/common`, or `packages/ui/src/common`
- Pass `className`, props, wrappers, or create a new variant instead of editing root shadcn primitives
- Consume shared UI via `import { … } from "ui"` (same in b2c, b2b, and any future app)

## Per-app divergence (what can differ)

Allowed to differ between `apps/b2c` and `apps/b2b`:

- Number of modules present
- Number of pages inside a module (e.g. `profile/pages/*`)
- Route groups and URL structure (e.g. one app may use `(protected)`, the other may not)
- `src/app/globals.css` CSS variable overrides (e.g. `--primary`)
- Copy/translations in `messages/*.json`
- next-intl `locales` list if a product truly needs different language coverage

NOT allowed to differ:

- Folder shape (`src/app`, `src/modules`, `src/shared`)
- Module contract (`components`, `hooks`, `services`, `types`, `pages`)
- Where API calls live (never in components; always in `src/shared/api` + `src/modules/*/services`)
- Shared primitive source (always `packages/ui`)
- ESLint/Prettier/TypeScript base config (always from `packages/config` + `tsconfig.base.json`)

## Rendering & state (every app)

- Default to server components
- SEO pages MUST NOT be client-only
- Prefer URL-driven state for filters/search
- Do NOT store server data in global client state without strong reason

## Adding a page (quick reference, any app in `apps/*`)

1. Create the page at `apps/<app>/src/modules/<product>/pages/<page-name>.tsx` (not in `src/app/`).
2. Supporting code stays in the same module: `components/`, `hooks/`, `services/`, `types/`.
3. New API calls live in `src/modules/<product>/services/*` and use the base client from `src/shared/api`. Never in a component.
4. Wire the route as a one-liner at `apps/<app>/src/app/[lang]/<segment>/page.tsx` that imports the page component.
5. Add translations to every locale in `apps/<app>/messages/<locale>.json`.

Anti-patterns (reject if seen):
- Page UI inside `apps/*/src/app/...`
- `fetch(...)` inside a React component
- Forking a `packages/ui` component per app
- Business logic placed in `src/shared/` instead of `src/modules/<product>/`

